                    <span>Just finished Menn's "All The Rave," a.k.a. the Napster chronicles....<P>for what it's worth, i found very little new material here - most of the scoop is previously published.... <P>& to my dismay, nothing is reported on Shawn Fanning's new venture, Snocap. An interesting twist for Shawn with Snocap, several journals are reporting that Fanning's new company seeks to end illegal file-swapping with an avalanche of controls...interesting twist, wouldn't you say for the guy who created fild-sharing to begin with...again nothing of this is reported in Menn's book which feels heavily dated by now.<P>At any rate, the book read kinda slow....though the thing i do appreciate the most is the book's cover art - kitty in black.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Fantastic book, well written, very imformative</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
